    39	
    40	### ADMS Push (Port 8085)
    41	
    42	- **What:** Device sends HTTP POST to `/iclock/cdata` with attendance records
    43	  as they are captured. The server runs an embedded ADMS listener.
    44	- **Trigger:** Every punch on the scanner.
    45	- **Data:** Real-time, single-punch events.
    46	- **Latency:** Sub-second.
    47	
    48	### SDK Pull (Configurable Interval)
    49	
    50	- **What:** Server calls `device.get_attendance(since: last_known_timestamp)`
    51	  to request all records the device has stored since the last pull.
    52	- **Trigger:** Periodic timer (configurable via `poll_interval_secs`).
    53	- **Data:** Bulk batches. Catches anything ADMS missed (network blips,
    54	  device buffer, reboots).
    55	- **Latency:** Up to `poll_interval_secs` seconds.
    56	
    57	### Why Both?
    58	
    59	| Concern | ADMS Push | SDK Pull |
    60	|---------|-----------|----------|
    61	| Real-time events | ✅ | ❌ (delayed by interval) |
    62	| Bulk historical data | ❌ (single events) | ✅ (batches) |
    63	| Survives network blips | ❌ (events lost during outage) | ✅ (device buffers records) |
    64	| Survives device reboot | ❌ | ✅ (pulls backlog) |
    65	| Firewall-friendly | ❌ (device needs outbound HTTP) | ✅ (server initiates) |
    66	
    67	### Poll Interval (`poll_interval_secs`)
    68	
    69	Controls how often the SDK pull loop queries each device.
    70	
    71	- **Default:** 60 seconds
    72	- **Minimum:** 5 seconds
    73	- **Maximum:** 3600 seconds (1 hour)
    74	- **Trade-off:** Lower = fresher data but more network traffic.
    75	  Higher = less traffic but longer gaps if ADMS push fails.
    76	
    77	### Dedup Guarantee
    78	
    79	The pipeline's dedup stage uses `(device_sn, user_pin, timestamp)` as the
    80	deduplication key. If the same punch arrives via both ADMS push and SDK pull,
    81	only one copy is stored. This is essential because both paths run concurrently.
    82	
    83	## System Settings
    84	
    85	These are engine-wide settings persisted in the `settings` table under
    86	the `"system"` key. They control behavior that applies to ALL devices.
    87	
    88	| Setting | Type | Default | Purpose |
    89	|---------|------|---------|---------|
    90	| `poll_interval_secs` | u32 | 60 | SDK pull frequency for all devices |
    91	| `auto_discover` | bool | false | UDP broadcast scan for new ZKTeco scanners on LAN |
    92	
    93	## Current Implementation Status
